Method Detail

workOnIt

void workOnIt(long jobId,
              java.lang.String consumerName,
              ArmyAudit audit,
              T dataToBeProcessed)

This operation can take a loooong long time!

Important: it MUST call ArmyAudit.aConsumerHasBeenFinishedHisJob(long, java.lang.String, boolean, br.fml.eti.behavior.BuildingException, java.lang.String) after the end of execution.

Parameters:
jobId - The job identity to be called by audit.
consumerName - To be used by the audit.
dataToBeProcessed - data (the "bullet")
audit - Interface to intercept details of processing. The specific implementation MUST call the method ArmyAudit.aConsumerHasBeenFinishedHisJob(long, java.lang.String, boolean, br.fml.eti.behavior.BuildingException, java.lang.String).
